# Qwertystock Marketing Positioning

- Qwertystock public marketing must consistently include these pillars: fresh/trending royalty-free catalog, no spam, no endless similars, contributor-first economics, and AI/embedding search.
- Core differentiator: position Qwertystock as an AI-search-first microstock built around semantic embeddings, not only exact keyword matching.
- When using the phrase "first in the world", treat it as marketing positioning unless separately verified for legal/compliance copy. Safer public copy can say "built as an AI-search microstock" or "AI-search-first microstock".
- Explain AI search in buyer language: it finds assets by meaning, scene, objects, mood, visual similarity, and multilingual intent even when exact keywords differ.
- Do not expose internal embedding scores, vector distances, MPR/RPM, or trend scores in public UI unless a separate product decision explicitly requires it.
- Marketing pages should use real Qwertystock catalog posters behind category/value cards where possible; avoid plain text-only blocks when the section sells a visual concept.
- Landing presentation zones must not reuse the same catalog asset across hero/mosaic, category cards, and value cards; repeated posters make the catalog look small and must be replaced with unique, topic-relevant assets.
- Keep the Qwertystock brand system: dark neutral shell, cyan/blue/violet QS accents, and pink only for primary commerce CTAs.

Production copy hygiene:

- Public pages must describe the buyer/author outcome, not the implementation. Do not mention internal hosts, server aliases, repo names, workers, queues, deployment hooks, env vars, monitoring bots, or provider API plumbing.
- Avoid production UI phrases such as `WAY`, `qwertydata`, `qwertysearch`, `PM2`, `nginx`, `Mongo`, `PostgreSQL`, `Namecheap API`, `OpenAI prompt`, `Detectron`, `IndexNow worker`, `sitemap watcher`, and `Telegram bot` unless the page is clearly admin/ops documentation.
- Use product wording instead: "подбираем домены", "проверяем цену", "готовим файл", "AI-поиск по смыслу", "семантический поиск", "статистика индексации".
- User-facing status messages should answer what is happening and what the user can do next. They should not reveal where or how the backend performs the step.
